Notes: The 'row_id' is a CSV internal identifier for the data row and does not correspond to any ontology property or related entity; thus, it maps directly to the main entity as an identifier placeholder.

'patient_id' clearly relates to the patient entity linked via the property AIDAVA:hasPatient from DrugPrescription; although no deeper path is provided, no 2-hop paths from Patient are listed, so this 1-hop path is optimal.

The ATC code relates to the prescribed medication, best modeled by linking to the sphn:Drug entity via sphn:hasDrug; while no 2-hop path from Drug is given, this path semantically fits medication identification better than any code or terminology property directly on DrugPrescription.

The diagnosis_code corresponds to the indication to start the drug, modeled as a sphn:Diagnosis entity linked via sphn:hasIndicationToStart; although there is an alternative path to sphn:Intent, Diagnosis is more appropriate for a clinical diagnosis code.
The creation_date is best represented by the property sphn:hasDateTime of type xsd:dateTime on DrugPrescription; no deeper 2-hop paths provide a better semantic fit for this timestamp.
The 'times_a_day' column represents frequency of administration, directly matching sphn:hasFrequency with range Quantity; no further 2-hop paths offer better context, so this 1-hop path is optimal.
'Dosage' corresponds to the prescribed quantity of the drug, best mapped to sphn:hasQuantity which points to a Quantity entity; no 2-hop paths offer better detail, so this direct path is selected.
